[{"id":"0abdbbab-feae-4f15-a1da-f970433057c3","type":"heading","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left","level":3,"isToggleable":false},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Technical Deep Dive: ","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":"handle_module","styles":{"code":true}}],"children":[]},{"id":"904a031b-8a8f-4e20-b078-5bbdf51a0e7d","type":"paragraph","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"handle_module","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" method is the high-level architect of the ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"ScopeManager","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":". Its role is to perform a pre-analysis "scan" of a Python file to discover its structural layout—identifying every class and function and mapping their nesting relationships before any deep data-flow analysis occurs.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"b696bcdf-6c3c-4b53-8053-5e98bb8541d8","type":"divider","props":{},"children":[]},{"id":"46110ed2-7d4c-4a30-9a63-a7dc698a918d","type":"heading","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left","level":3,"isToggleable":false},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works","styles":{"bold":true}}],"children":[]},{"id":"b0dd7ebc-bdff-4a08-a933-c5ed5e452156","type":"paragraph","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"This method utilizes a recursive internal function named ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"process","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and leverages Python's built-in ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"symtable","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" (Symbol Table) library. The process follows these steps:","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"86b06e39-898c-475a-acb9-72fc4c6ab5bc","type":"numberedListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Symbol Table Generation","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":": It converts the raw source code (","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"contents","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":") into a ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"symtable","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" object. This is more efficient than a full AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) traversal for the specific task of identifying scopes and variable visibility.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"607083ff-5956-41bd-b6e1-fb05a52d2fb0","type":"numberedListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Namespace Construction","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":":","styles":{}}],"children":[{"id":"f9417914-b4e4-4a77-a969-08ffe04afaa3","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For the top-level module, it uses the provided ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"modulename","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":".","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"841ff2be-6c37-4f19-9ee1-4b4b63d6529e","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"As it dives into nested structures, it uses ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"utils.join_ns","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" to build fully qualified names (e.g., ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"app.models.User.save_login","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":").","styles":{}}],"children":[]}]},{"id":"55ab3bcf-5b7b-466d-b8ca-b67bcef2b84c","type":"numberedListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Identification","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":": It checks the type of each symbol table entry. If it encounters a ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":""function"","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" or ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":""class"","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":", it adds the full namespace to the tracking lists (","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"functions","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" or ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"classes","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":").","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"ab1946a1-99c7-4f17-9e24-86c97ea491f0","type":"numberedListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scope Creation","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":": For every block discovered (including the module itself), it calls ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"self.create_scope(fullns, parent)","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":". This initializes a ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"ScopeItem","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" and links it to its enclosing environment.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"83ae86ea-e79e-41fc-a369-4aa6b4c88712","type":"numberedListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Recursion","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":": It calls ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"process","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" on all children of the current table, ensuring that even deeply nested functions (closures) or inner classes are captured and correctly parented.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"aeb25c80-864b-4f2b-aba9-85070a75ebca","type":"divider","props":{},"children":[]},{"id":"94a9ef96-4e81-481a-9b6d-6c63fa3f56e5","type":"heading","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left","level":3,"isToggleable":false},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Logic: The ","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":"process","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" Closure","styles":{"bold":true}}],"children":[]},{"id":"3cd69167-01dd-4494-80dc-8dcee8e3832f","type":"paragraph","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The internal ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"process(namespace, parent, table)","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" function is where the structural mapping happens:","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"aa75e756-e1bb-4e86-9471-85a0f41eb113","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"namespace","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":": The prefix inherited from the parent.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"9ba8b6e7-afca-4c4f-a84d-fa0e3c6b5c7b","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"parent","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":": The actual ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"ScopeItem","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" instance of the enclosing block.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"5e21731f-bb2c-415d-ae78-57edd47ba7d8","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"table","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":": The current segment of the symbol table being analyzed.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"3043af47-8742-4c24-97f1-5023aae01432","type":"paragraph","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"By passing the ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"sc","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" (the current scope created) as the ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"parent","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" to the next recursive call, it builds the hierarchical "link" that allows for later name resolution.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"9318262e-56b3-456c-b3a9-bd350822f2c6","type":"divider","props":{},"children":[]},{"id":"258a8d01-906a-4535-ac52-899c48c17c77","type":"heading","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left","level":3,"isToggleable":false},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Is This Method Important?","styles":{"bold":true}}],"children":[]},{"id":"9974e0d5-4592-45f6-9690-bf7f9ac28100","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Foundation for Resolution","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":": Without the tree built here, the ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"get_def","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" method wouldn't know which scope is the "parent" of another, making it impossible to resolve global or non-local variables.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"84d36404-0561-4955-ba03-6dee9b7be961","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pre-Discovery","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":": It returns a dictionary containing all discovered function and class namespaces. This allows the main analyzer to know exactly which entities need to be visited and analyzed in subsequent passes.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"81b12656-4d1d-4f77-9eaf-ae0fe5f4928a","type":"bulletListItem","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Namespace Integrity","styles":{"bold":true}},{"type":"text","text":": By using ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"utils.join_ns","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" during this structural discovery, it ensures that every symbol in the project has a unique, predictable, and fully-qualified identity.","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"c6526f6d-48f2-4492-ad32-305a7e33ca3b","type":"divider","props":{},"children":[]},{"id":"3c5d49f5-97c4-4b1a-b6f1-6522708f2950","type":"heading","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left","level":3,"isToggleable":false},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example Result","styles":{"bold":true}}],"children":[]},{"id":"05821fbb-1bfb-4b78-80b9-be915dfa77c6","type":"paragraph","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"handle_module","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" processes a file with a class containing a method, the returned dictionary would look like:","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"53520fc4-dac6-40ef-b4f3-e2a9cdce249f","type":"codeBlock","props":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{
    "functions": ["my_mod.MyClass.my_method"],
    "classes": ["my_mod.MyClass"]
}","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"ee73fc4b-9adc-47dd-b01f-505ccfddecdd","type":"paragraph","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simultaneously, the ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"ScopeManager","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" would now hold three ","styles":{}},{"type":"text","text":"ScopeItem","styles":{"code":true}},{"type":"text","text":" objects: the module, the class (parented to the module), and the method (parented to the class).","styles":{}}],"children":[]},{"id":"5ca38d9f-c892-406e-827a-7d78db3e21f6","type":"paragraph","props":{"backgroundColor":"default","textColor":"default","textAlignment":"left"},"content":[],"children":[]}]
